description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a rare opportunity for an RMN to join the team at The Orchard in Lancaster.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At Lancashire and South Cumbria Foundation Trust (LSCFT), we are passionate about the quality of care we deliver and are looking for nurses who can help deliver excellent care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you a compassionate, respectful team player committed to promoting excellence, teamwork and accountability?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Do you have excellent communication skills that would enable you to work within a challenging environment that constantly strives to provide the best possible experience for our service users and their carers?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Learning Disability Nurses are welcome to apply and would be expected to work on the ward to form part of the qualified nurse’s establishment&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a nurse in LSCFT you will be central to providing high quality care and be given opportunities to develop your skills and knowledge. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for nurses who are passionate about people and delivering high quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You may also be eligible for a Relocation Package or Golden Hello incentives (subject to confirmation). Apply now for further details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Margaret Jenkins on 01524 550500&lt;/p&gt;
